Citation.sTitle: The (p, rho, T, x) properties for (propane + n-butane + isobutane) ternary mixtures over the temperature range from (280 to 440) K at pressures from (1 to 200) MPa
Citation.sAbstract: The (p, ?, T, x) properties for (propane + n-butane + isobutane) ternary mixtures in the compressed liquid phase were measured by means of a metal-bellows variable volumometer over the temperature range from (280 to 440) K at pressures from (1 to 200) MPa. The mole fraction purities of the propane, n-butane, and isobutane used in the measurements were 0.9999, 0.9997, and 0.9999, respectively. The expanded uncertainties (k = 2) in temperature, pressure, density, and composition measurements have been estimated to be less than +-3 mK; 1.4 kPa (p 7 MPa), 0.06% (7 MPa less than p 50 MPa), 0.1% (50 MPa less than p 150 MPa), and 0.2% (p greater than 150 MPa); 0.09%; and 4.4 * 10-4, respectively. In the region above 100 MPa at T = (280 and 440) K, the uncertainty in density measurements increases from 0.09% to 0.13% and 0.22%, respectively. Comparisons of the available equation of state with the present measurements are reported. On the basis of the present results, the excess molar volume of the mixtures was calculated and illustrated as a function of temperature and pressure.
